Kathryn Zaremba https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kathryn_Zaremba 0 Kathryn Lauren Zaremba (born September 24, 1983) is an American writer, illustrator, surface designer, business woman, and former actress and singer. She is best known for her roles as Annie Warbucks in the 1993 musical Annie Warbucks and Lisa Leeper on Full House. Zaremba also co-starred on Bringing up Jack and The Jeff Foxworthy Show, as well as making several appearances on Sisters. Her last professional screen acting credit was the 1997 Disney television film Toothless, starring Kirstie Alley. She retired from acting and singing when she was 14.Zaremba is a graduate of Broken Arrow Senior High School. She is an alumna of Kansas City Art Institute and Corcoran College of Art and Design. Zaremba works as an illustrator and surface designer. She married Jeremy Ney in 2010 and they live in Washington, D.C., where she runs her business, Kate Zaremba Company. She also co runs The Lemon Bowl. Kathryn_Lauren_Zaremba ( born September_24 , 1983 ) is an_American_writer , illustrator , surface_designer , business_woman , and former_actress_and_singer .
